author: Inside Edition
description: Authorities say a motorcyclist ran a red light and hit a car broadside before a fireball erupted and a second biker went flying. The motorcycle rider was in flames. The stricken biker rolled over to extinguish the flames and his friend took off his burning pants. The only injuries the rider in flames sustained was a broken ankle and minor burns. Brianna Vargas, who was behind the wheel of the car, spoke with Inside Edition.
title: Fireball Erupts After Motorcyclist Crashed Into Car

author: Inside Edition
description: Real Housewives of Beverly Hills stars Kathy Hilton and Sutton Stracke are the newest celebrities to find their homes targeted by burglars while out of town. Both Hilton and Stracke were at BravoCon in Las Vegas, a heavily-publicized event. On Saturday night, Rick Hilton called 911 and said three burglars were inside the family home. When cops came, the burglars apparently had escaped. Stracke's dogwalker called 911 about a broken window when cops arrived and took a police report.
title: Real Housewives Of Beverly Hills Stars Targeted By Burglars

author: Inside Edition
description: Paris Hilton is speaking out about a claim that she was targeted by Ghislaine Maxwell as a potential "date" for Jeffrey Epstein. In 2000 when Hilton was 19, she was apparently spotted by Maxwell at a party during fashion week in New York. Now, Hilton says she has no recollection of that night. However, Hilton and Maxwell did cross paths: a photograph from that party shows them together with Donald Trump. On Sunday night, Trump announced that the Epstein files should be released.
title: Paris Hilton Says She Does Not Remember Ever Meeting Ghislaine Maxwell

author: Inside Edition
description: Five months ago, 10-year-old Leah Lendel was snorkeling with her family in shallow water in Florida, when a bull shark chomped down on her wrist. Leah was airlifted to Tampa General, surprising everyone with how calm she was. Doctors reattached the girl's hand in a surgery that took 6 hours. Leah and her mother Nadia spoke exclusively with Inside Edition's anchor Eva Pilgrim. The family has set up a GoFundMe to help with recovery costs. To learn more, click this link: https://bit.ly/482Ysxq
title: Young Shark Attack Survivor Details Recovery In Exclusive Interview

author: Inside Edition
description: A nationwide uproar is erupting over Megyn Kelly's remarks suggesting that Jeffrey Epstein was not a pedophile. "He was into the barely legal type, he liked 15-year-old girls and I realize this is disgusting. I'm definitely not trying to make an excuse for this," Kelly said. "I'm just giving you facts."  The hashtag IWasFifteen is now trending on social media. The women of "The View," and actresses Melissa Gilbert and Cynthia Nixon also joined the chorus of condemnation.
title: Uproar After Megyn Kelly Suggests Jeffrey Epstein Was Not A Pedophile

author: Inside Edition
description: A teen was rescued from freezing water in New York City by brave police officers. The NYPD says the girl jumped into the Harlem River in an apparent suicide attempt, which she seemed to instantly regret as she screamed for help. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: NYPD Rescues Teen From Freezing Harlem River

author: Inside Edition
description: New York Jets cornerback Kris Boyd had just left an Asian fusion restaurant in midtown Manhattan early Sunday morning when shots rang out. Boyd was struck by at least one bullet. He rushed to nearby Bellevue Hospital, where he remains in critical condition. It's unclear if Boyd was a target in the shooting. The NYPD released images of a man wanted for questioning in the case. Police are also searching for two cars, a BMW and a Mercedes, that fled the scene.
title: NFL Player Kris Boyd In Critical Condition After Manhattan Shooting

author: Inside Edition
description: Grace Meyers from Michigan is living with Marfan syndrome. The inherited disorder affects someone's connective tissue and comes with several life-threatening medical complications.
title: Woman With Marfan Syndrome Could Tear Aorta At Any Moment #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: These nurses saved people while off the clock. In October, Candace Dodge and her dad were at a Buffalo Bills game when his heart stopped beating. And nurse Danielle Johnson stepped in. Registered nurse Danya Topham performed CPR at a softball field while watching her sons play. In October, ER Nurse Nick Arreola saved a family of five from their blazing home on his way home from his shift. Inside Edition Digital's Andrea Swindall has more.
title: Hero Nurses Who Saved People While They Were Off The Clock
